Silent Warrior:<br><br>
You know what alcohol does to a guy trying to forget, deny etc. Well, an alcoholic is the same same.. beaucoup same same as a WORKAHOLIC.. the same road..just different car.<br>
It's bad when I guy gets caught in both traps... your work suffers if you drink too much and your drinking suffers if you work too much.<br>
You are (to me) a performance objective type person...you may feel worthless unless you fly faster than everyone else...and have a bigger watch.  It is a fear type motivation.  On the x and y axis you take off on a perfect 45 degree climb.  The more fear...the more motivation.  It works great on the low end but eventually... too much fear stops the motivation.  We don't taper off on the curve...we plunge to the bottom.  Sort of like a reverse flow in the axial compressors... a flame out.<br>
While you're standing there picking your nose and scratching your butt...take time to realize that you are a hell of a man, a very good person, and a well loved friend.. for no reason.. you just are and can't help it.<br>
Native American warriors were victims of external loci.. they were constantly proving themselves to the people by deeds, generosity, fiercness and admirable act of courage and strength.  The successful transition from &quot;My daddy can kick your daddy's ass,&quot; allowed those warriors who survive to become (in a graceful process) old geezers who loved to play with the children, spend time with the young horses, smell the flowers... and chuckle at the antics of the struggling young men.<br>
You've paid your dues..Tote Lam Pipe Driver.  Old warriors can lift their heads with pride.. without having to steal anymore horses.<br><br>
I am Tatekahomni Wambli, Whirlwind Eagle.. I am your brother forever.
